40|$|We {{present a}} divide-and-conquer {{version of the}} Cylindrical Algebraic Decomposition (CAD) {{algorithm}}. The algorithm represents the input as a <b>Boolean</b> <b>combination</b> of subformulas, computes cylindrical algebraic decompositions of solution sets of the subformulas, and combines the results. We propose a graph-based heuristic to find a suitable partitioning of the input and present empirical comparison with direct CAD computation...|$|E
